---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import BrandMark from '../components/BrandMark.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---
<BaseLayout>
  <Header>
    <BrandMark slot="mark" />
  </Header>

  <main>
    <section class="section hero-section">
      <div class="shell surface-dark pad hero-card">
        <div>
          <div class="meta-label">About</div>
          <h1 class="page-hero-title">Pre-release. Cross-runtime from the start.</h1>
          <p class="page-copy">
            Aster is at version 0.1-alpha. Python and TypeScript are the first-class alpha
            bindings today. The architecture, trust model, contract identity system, and
            wire protocol are implemented and tested, with additional language bindings in progress.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="shell grid grid-3">
        <article class="card surface-light light-card">
          <div class="meta-label">Current status</div>
           <h2 class="page-card-title">0.1-alpha — implemented and tested</h2>
           <p class="page-card-copy">Core RPC (unary, server streaming, client streaming, bidirectional streaming). Session-scoped services with state persistence. Four-gate trust model with enrollment credentials. BLAKE3 contract identity. Decentralised registry on iroh-docs/blobs/gossip. Apache Fory XLANG serialization. Wire-protocol conformance tests.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card surface-light light-card">
          <div class="meta-label">Today</div>
           <h2 class="page-card-title">Python and TypeScript alpha bindings</h2>
           <p class="page-card-copy">The current alpha surface includes Python and TypeScript bindings over the shared Aster model: iroh QUIC transport, Apache Fory codec, language-native service definitions, streaming RPC patterns, and async-first client/server APIs.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card surface-light light-card">
          <div class="meta-label">What comes next</div>
           <h2 class="page-card-title">More languages, CLI tools, production hardening</h2>
           <p class="page-card-copy">Java, .NET, Kotlin, and Go bindings are in progress. Rust is planned. CLI tools for key management, contract publication, and registry interaction continue to harden alongside the trust and session lifecycle.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="shell surface-dark pad link-card">
        <div>
          <div class="meta-label">Next stops</div>
           <h2 class="page-section-title">Read the spec. Explore the code. Check the docs.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="links">
          <a href="https://docs.aster.site">Docs</a>
          <a href="https://github.com/aster-rpc">GitHub</a>
          <a href="https://github.com/aster-rpc/spec">Specification</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .pad { padding: 26px; }
  .hero-section { padding-top: 24px; }
  .hero-card h1 { max-width: 11ch; color: var(--cloud-strong); }
  .hero-card p { margin-top: 14px; max-width: 62ch; color: var(--mist); }
  .grid { display: grid; gap: 16px; }
  .grid-3 { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr)); }
  .card { border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: 22px; }
  .light-card { border: 1px solid rgba(25, 37, 51, 0.1); }
  .meta-label { margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.2; letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .card h2, .link-card h2 { color: var(--ink); }
  .card p { color: var(--ink-soft); }
  .link-card { display: grid; gap: 18px; }
  .link-card h2 { color: var(--cloud-strong); }
  .links { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 12px; }
  .links a { border-radius: 999px; padding: 12px 14px; border: 1px solid var(--border-dark); color: var(--cloud-strong); background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03); }
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .grid-3 { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .pad { padding: 22px; }
  }
</style>
